      <text>Differentiation: Finding the Derivative of an Expression</text>
    </name>
    <questiontext format="moodle_auto_format">
      <text><![CDATA[<p>Find \(\displaystyle \frac{dy}{dx}\) for \({@expr@}\)</p>
<p><b>Step 1:</b> Differentiate both sides with respect to \(x\), yields to.</p>
<br> ( [[input:ans1]] ) \( \cdot \displaystyle \frac{dy}{dx} +\) [[input:ans1s]] [[feedback:prt1]]
<br> [[validation:ans1]]     [[validation:ans1s]] 

<p><b>Step 2:</b> The final step is to deduce \(\displaystyle \frac{dy}{dx}\).</p>
<br>\(\displaystyle \frac{dy}{dx}=\) [[input:ans2]] [[validation:ans2]] [[feedback:prt2]]]]></text>
    </questiontext>
    <generalfeedback format="moodle_auto_format">
      <text><![CDATA[<h3>Worked solution</h3>
<p> Recall the following derivations of functions</p>
<div>
